Fig. 5b illustrates that the proposed biosensor exhibits linear chronoamperometric response to glucose concentration in two ranges of 2 to 10 μM and 0.02 to 3 mM. The linear regression equation is as follows: I (μA) = 15.12 C[G

   lucose

](mM) − 3.19 (R2 = 0.993) and I (μA) = 0.663 C[G

   lucose

](mM) − 3.02 (R2 = 0.999), respectively. The sensitivity of the sensor was calculated to be 1512.4 μA mM−1 cm−2 and the limit of detection was calculated to be 0.7 μM. The analytical performance statistics for some reported biosensors for the determination of glucose are summarized in Table S3. It can be seen that the sensitivity of the AuNPs/N-GQDs-P-MOF-based biosensor has significant advantages compared with those of published methods.
